
Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)


Amazon EC2 provides scalable virtual servers in the cloud. It allows you to launch, manage, and configure instances without needing physical hardware. EC2 helps organizations run websites, applications, backend services, and more.



What I Learned
How to launch and configure EC2 instances

Understanding instance types and AMIs

Using key pairs to connect securely

Managing security groups

Basic Linux commands on an EC2 instance

Starting, stopping, and terminating instances



Why EC2 Matters


EC2 gives flexible, scalable compute power and is a core part of most cloud architectures.




















